# Final Acceptance Criteria

The implementation will be considered complete only when:

- Every public-facing image is editable from the CMS.
- Every logo is centrally managed.
- Every downloadable asset is centrally managed.
- No hardcoded media paths remain.
- Assets can be replaced without breaking relationships.
- Media usage is traceable.
- Unsafe deletion is prevented.
- Storage is abstracted.
- Responsive image delivery is operational.
- The system passes functional, performance, security and regression testing.
- The architecture is approved as production-ready.

